From Edward Ted Fischer Subject Re Notes on Jays Indians Series In article Edward Ouellette writes My point RBI might not be a perfect stat but nothing And no stat or lack of can tell me there are no clutch Maybe no stat CAN tell me either but some people I just know it I was hoping somebody would mention Clutch Baerga The two words simply do not go With runners in scoring position Baerga batted last This doesn't quite suck but most batters hit better in this Alomar He hit with runners in scoring position The difference Alomar had RBIs in such Baerga had RBIs in such Baerga got more chances yet succeeded only more Frankly I don't believe in But if I did my vote would go to Alomar for MVP let alone best in the AL Valentine